import "./scope.rq" as scope

activation {
    VS Code loads the extension host entry at ["../../packages/extension/src/extension/main.ts"] when an activation event in ["../../packages/extension/package.json"] matches.
    The exported `activate(context)` function is the single activation entry point for [scope.vscode_extension].
}

activation_events {
    Activation is declared in `contributes.activationEvents` in ["../../packages/extension/package.json"].
    - `onStartupFinished` â€” activate after the workbench finishes starting; ensures first-run onboarding can run without opening a `.rq` file first.
    - `onLanguage:reqlan` â€” activate when a reqlan document is opened.
    - `onLanguage:python`, `onLanguage:javascript`, `onLanguage:typescript`, `onLanguage:typescriptreact` â€” activate for comment-reference and glue-semantics support in those languages.
    - `onView:reqlan.activityBar` â€” activate when the Reqlan activity bar view is opened.
    - `onChatParticipant:reqlan.reqlan` â€” activate when the @reqlan chat participant is used.
    - `onCommand:reqlan.*` â€” activate when listed Reqlan palette commands run before the extension has loaded.
    There is no separate `onInstall` hook; install-time behaviour runs on the first activation after install.
}

activation_sequence {
    `activate` runs the following phases in ["../../packages/extension/src/extension/main.ts"]:
    1. Register reference inlay-hint configuration synchronously.
    2. Await [analytical_submodule_activation] â€” registers commands, activity bar, chat, webviews, AI commands, and mutation hooks before awaiting index startup.
    3. Register import-error quick-fix commands when the analytical submodule started.
    4. Await language-client startup for LSP features.
    5. Register attribute and name catalog sync when both the language client and index are available.
    6. Invoke [onboarding_check] without awaiting it, so onboarding cannot block activation.
    Submodule and language-client failures are logged and do not prevent later phases from running.
}

analytical_submodule_activation {
    Analytical submodule startup is implemented in ["../../packages/extension/src/analytical_submodule/index.ts"].
    VS Code contributions (commands, activity bar provider, chat participant, webviews, AI commands, mutation hooks) register synchronously at the start of `activateAnalyticalSubmodule`.
    Index activation is awaited afterward so the sidebar can render while indexing continues.
}

onboarding_check {
    Post-install onboarding is checked on every activation, not via a dedicated install event.
    ["./onboarding/page-thanks-for-installing.rq".installation_event_trigger] is satisfied because `activate` always calls ["../../packages/extension/src/extension/open-thanks-for-installing.ts"].
    The check reads global state key `onboarding` via ["../../packages/extension/src/extension/onboarding-state.ts"]:
    - `onboardingMessageShown` â€” when false, open the built ["../../packages/extension/media/thanks-for-installing.rq"] as an untitled `.rq` editor.
    - `lastVersion` â€” updated each activation after the message has been shown so future releases can detect extension updates.
    The call is fire-and-forget; errors are logged and do not fail activation.
}
